Examples how to use Pythia8:
* main01.cc & main01.cmnd: extensive tests and event properties
* main02.cc & ttsample.init & ttsample.evnt & main02for.f: 
    input of LHA events from files
* main03.cc: LHA tricked to study fixed parton configurations
* main04.cc: how to link an external decay handler
* main05.cc: how to link an external random number generator
* main06.cc: brief example with Z0 pT spectrum
* main07.cc & main07.cmnd: simplified copy of main01
* main08.cc & ttsample.init & ttsample.evnt: simplified copy of main02 
* main09.cc: LEP events with sphericity analysis
* main10.cc: cell jet analysis of LHC events
* main11.cc & main11.cmnd: output to HepMC event record format
* main12.cc & main12.cmnd: Pythia8 vs. Pythia6 cross sections

Type "gmake mainNN" (or "gmake main02for") to build an executable.
Type "./mainNN.exe > outputfile" to run program. 
Type "gmake clean" to clean up the examples directory (but not output files).